tracks.key: Augustus (JAMg)
tracks.label: AUGUSTUS_JAMg

metadata.Publication status: unpublished - please follow Toronto/Ft. Lauderdale conditions of data re-use
metadata.Data description: Augustus prediction components that were generated and used by the JAMg pipeline. Augustus was trained with high quality gene models generated by Trinity RNA-Seq and PASA2 and these evidence 'hints' were used: RNASeq coverage, transcriptome assemblies, RepeatMasker, Transposon and UniProt searches on predicted exons.

tracks.key: JAMg Consensus Gene Set v1
tracks.label: JAMg_v1

metadata.Publication status: unpublished - please follow Toronto/Ft. Lauderdale conditions of data re-use
metadata.Data description: Consensus gene set generated by Alexie Papanicolaou and Just_Annotated_My_genome – using 3 publicly available RNA-Seq libraries and several private ones (gut and reproductive tissues of adults) from Oberhofer. Method is based on i) de-novo predictions with Augustus, Glimmer, SNAP, GeneMark, ii) RNA-Seq using Trinity RNASeq de-novo and Trinity Genome Guided, iii) PASA2 RNASeq integration and iv) Evidence Modeller. Full method available on http://jamg.sourceforge.net

tracks.key: GC Content

metadata.Track legend: Visualization of GC/AT content in the reference assembly.  Bases called as G or C are scored 1 and colored blue; A and T bases are scored 0 and colored yellow. Ambiguous bases (N) are left blank. At zoom levels in which individual bases can not be resolved, scores are averaged for visualization. The pivot point is 0.5, or 50% G+C or A+T. The score at any position may be seen by moving the cursor to that position in the track.
metadata.Track description: This track was created as part of the data proccessing workflow used to create the Web Apollo instance.

metadata.Data description: 06 Dec 2015: This track reconciles the two OGS tracks produced by JAMg (v1) and NCBI (v2) and bring in the manual curation track. For every locus, a 2-2 comparison was made and then one gene was kept in that order: manual curation that have been approved, NCBI and JAMg. No alternative splice genes were kept.
